title: Arugula Salad With Pine Nuts, Parmesan, And Grilled Peaches
summary: Arugula Salad With Pine Nuts, Parmesan, And Grilled Peaches is a gluten free and primal main course. One portion of this dish contains about 14g of protein, 19g of fat, and a total of 262 calories. This recipe serves 4 and costs $1.92 per serving. 1 person has made this recipe and would make it again. A mixture of pine nuts, parmesan cheese, peaches, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. To use up the peaches you could follow this main course with the Easy As Pie Peaches as a dessert. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about 45 minutes. It can be enjoyed any time, but it is especially good for The Fourth Of July. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 66%. This score is solid. Try Grilled Pesto Chicken Pasta Salad with Sun-Dried Tomatoes, Arugulan and Pine Nuts, Arugula-Basil Pesto with Pine Nuts, Parmesan and Ricotta, and Arugula Salad With Fennel And Pine Nuts for similar recipes.
